{
    "identity": "nprot-142",
    "title": "Generation of pDRf1-GW",
    "content": [
        {
            "header": "Introduction",
            "content": "For rapid cloning of genes of interest into a yeast expression vector, the Gateway<sup>TM</sup> technology can be used."
        },
        {
            "header": "Procedure",
            "content": "1)  pDRf1-GW is a yeast shuttle vector carrying a GATEWAY\nTM\ncloning cassette \\(Invitrogen, Carlsbad, CA) and an f1 viral replication origin. Generate pDRf1-GW by substituting a SpeI-SalI fragment from pDR196\n1\nwith a new multi-cloning sequence \\(SpeI, EcoRI, NotI, PstI, SalI). \r\n\n\n2)  Amplify by PCR a 500bp DNA fragment containing the f1 replication origin from pGEM-T-easy \\(Promega, Madison, WI).  Use  primers containing a HindIII restriction site, and then clone into the HindIII site located upstream of the PMA1 promoter fragment to generate the pDRf1 vector. \r\n\n\n3)  Amplify the GATEWAY\nTM\nfragment by PCR with primers containing an EcoRV site and clone in a blunt-ended NotI site in pDRf1 to generate pDRf1-GW."
        },
        {
            "header": "References",
            "content": "Rentsch, D. _et al._ NTR1 encodes a high affinity oligopeptide transporter in Arabidopsis. _FEBS Lett._ **370**, 264-268 \\(1995)."
        }
    ],
